<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
	<title><%= client %>: <%= project %>-<%= concept %>banners</title>
	<link href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto:400,400italic,100,100italic,700,300,300italic' rel='stylesheet' type='text/css'>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href=".strategist/preview/preview-assets/app.min.css">
</head>
<body>
	<header>
		<h1><%= client %>: <%= project %>-<%= concept %>banners</h1>
	</header>
	<div class="wrapper">
		<div class="main">
			<div class="disclaimer">
				<h2>Gulp Tasks Available:</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><em>gulp default</em>&mdash;If you've just run this task, animate the first size of each concept. The first size is the first size you have listed in <strong>config.json</strong> file.</li>
					<li><em>gulp resize</em>&mdash;Run this task after you've animated the first size of each concept. It will create all other sizes for each concept, based on the first animated size.</li>
					<li><em>gulp preview</em>&mdash;Run this task to generate the preview that you may need to send out for review. </li>
					<li><em>gulp handoff</em>&mdash;Run this task after you're ready to send the banners to a vendor or network.</li>
				</ul>
				<h2>Other Tasks: </h2>
				<ul>
					<li><em>gulp clean</em>&mdash;Run this task if you'd like to start over. It clears out all your added files except files you may have placed in assets/*</li>
					<li><em>gulp watch</em>&mdash;This task automatically runs after running <em>gulp default</em>. However, you will need to stop it (ctrl + c) before you can run the other tasks. To continue having your banners live-reload, simply run this task again.</li>
					<li><em>gulp check-file-size</em>&mdash;This task automatically runs while running <em>gulp watch</em> AND each time you save a banner file. If you are over the max file size allotted for the banners, it will display a console warning with the size of banner (including html, js libs, and imagesâ€“all compressed).</li>
				</ul>
				<br>
			</div>

			<div class="animated">

				<h2>Banners</h2>
				<ul>
					<% for(var c = 0; c <= concepts.length; c++ ) { var concept = concepts[c]; %>
							<% if (concept !== undefined) { %>
								<% for(var s = 0; s <= sizes.length; s++ ) { var size = sizes[s]; %>
									<% if (size !== undefined) { %>
									<li><a target="_blank" href="banners/<%= concept %>/<%= size.name %>/index.html"><%= concept %>-<%= size.name %></a></li>
								<% } %>
							<% } %>
						<% } %>
					<% } %>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>
